Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a software application using an evolutionary algorithm for predicting student failure rate at school. This involves the use of machine learning techniques such as genetic programming, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application also involves the use of optimization techniques, which can be classified under computational engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of artificial neural networks and fuzzy logic systems, which are subfields of neural networks (cs.NE) and software engineering (cs.SE), respectively.
